# {{ project_name }} — Agent Guide (Claude)

This project uses the **morpheus-platform** (`v{{ platform_version | default("0.1.0") }}`)
via the **brownfield overlay**. The overlay does not touch source directories;
it only adds `.agent/`, root pointer files, and additive `.github/` helpers.

## Start here

- **Project law:** [`.agent/constitution.md`](./.agent/constitution.md). Binding
  for every agent acting on this repo. Read before editing code.
- **Skills catalog:** [`.agent/skills/`](./.agent/skills/). Invoke by name; each
  skill's frontmatter declares `when_to_use`, `when_not_to_use`, and
  `requires_profiles`.
- **Feature templates:** [`.agent/feature-template/`](./.agent/feature-template/)
  for PRD, spec, plan, and tasks stubs.
- **Platform manifest:** `platform-manifest.json` — installed profile, stacks,
  workspace, PM, git provider.
- **Brownfield notes:** [`.agent/BROWNFIELD_NOTES.md`](./.agent/BROWNFIELD_NOTES.md)
  — what the overlay backed up and where.

## Conventions for agents working on this project

1. Read the constitution first. Cite it when proposing a non-trivial change.
2. Use the skills in `.agent/skills/`; do not reinvent them.
3. Respect composition rules: exactly one workspace, exactly one git provider,
   0..1 PM, 0..N stacks, 0..N domains.
4. Never edit `platform-manifest.json` by hand — run the CLI's update flow.
5. Never delete `.pre-morpheus.bak` files without explicit steward approval;
   they are the only record of what this repo looked like before the overlay.

## When the project changes

If a new stack, workspace, or integration is added, re-run
`agentic init --resume` so the manifest, skills, and templates stay in sync.

